    <h1>Introduction</h1>
    <p>Your mission is simple: Become a <strong>haploid gamete</strong> ‚Äî either a sperm or an egg ‚Äî and form a new <strong>zygote</strong>. Right now, you're a diploid cell, carrying 46 chromosomes (23 pairs), made of tightly coiled DNA. Through this game, you'll reduce your chromosome number by half to become ready for <strong>fertilization</strong>.</p>
    <p>Let's dive in and explore how meiosis works to create genetic diversity!</p>
    <button onclick="nextPage()">Continue</button>
  </div>

  <!-- Interphase Page -->
  <div class="page" id="page3">
    <h1>Interphase</h1>
    <p>You are now in <strong>Interphase</strong>, the longest phase of the cell cycle. This is where you‚Äôll spend about <strong>90%</strong> of your time! In the <strong>G1 and G2</strong>, you‚Äôre growing and preparing your organelles for division. During the <strong>S (synthesis)</strong> phase, your DNA is replicated, forming identical sister chromatids, ready for the next steps in division.</p>
    <div class="img-container">
      <img src="https://images.saymedia-content.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:eco%2Cw_456/MTc0NjM4OTA0MzIwODYyMTUz/stages-of-the-cell-cycle-mitosis-part-1-of-2.webp" alt="Interphase">
