<div class="page" id="page4" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: center; padding: 50px; background-color: #f0f8ff;">
  <h1 style="font-size: 3em; margin-bottom: 10px;">‚ûî Mutation</h1>
  <h2 style="font-size: 2em; color: #ff4c4c; margin-bottom: 30px;">Oops! Something changed in your DNA!</h2>

  <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin: 20px auto; max-width: 800px;">
    <strong>Mutations</strong> are changes in your <strong>DNA sequence</strong>, which can occur during the <strong>Synthesis (S) phase</strong> of the cell cycle, when your DNA is being <strong>replicated</strong>.
  </p>

  <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin: 20px auto; max-width: 800px;">
    These changes can sometimes lead to <strong>genetic disorders</strong>, or even contribute to evolution by creating new traits.
  </p>

  <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin: 20px auto; max-width: 800px;">
    Most mutations don‚Äôt have an impact, but some can be harmful or beneficial, depending on the type and location.
  </p>

