  <!-- Prophase I -->
  <div class="page" id="page6">
    <h1>‚ûî Prophase I</h1>
    <p>In <strong>Prophase</strong> I of meiosis, chromosomes become visible as they <strong>condense</strong>, and the <strong>nuclear envelope</strong> begins to break down. The <strong>centrioles</strong> move to opposite sides of the cell, and <strong>spindle fibers</strong> start to form, preparing for the division process.</p>
    <div class="img-container">
      <img src="https://api.www.labxchange.org/api/v1/xblocks/lb:LabXchange:bc646043:lx_image:1/storage/lxc_p74_chromosomal-mutations_rearrangements_snapshot-1_april2024-e7a0a0b1aa702b3b4033980ef3dde504.png" alt="Prophase I">
    </div>
