  <!-- Page 9: Metaphase I -->
  <div class="page" id="page9">
    <h1>‚ûî Metaphase I</h1>
    <p>During  <strong>Metaphase</strong> I of meiosis, the <strong>tetrads</strong> line up along the <strong>metaphase plate</strong> in the center of the cell. Each <strong>homologous</strong> chromosome is attached to <strong>spindle fibers</strong> from opposite <strong>poles</strong>. This alignment ensures that each new cell will receive one chromosome from each <strong>homologous pair</strong>.</p>


    <p style="font-weight: bold; color: #222; background-color: #ff3b86; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;">
      üöÄ Drag and drop the events happening during Metaphase I!
    </p>


