  <!-- Page 10: Anaphase I -->
  <div class="page" id="page10">
    <h1>‚ûî Anaphase I</h1>
    <p>During <strong>Anaphase</strong> I of meiosis, the <strong>homologous</strong> chromosomes are <strong>pulled</strong> apart by the <strong>spindle fibers</strong>. Each chromosome, consisting of two sister chromatids, moves <strong>towards</strong> opposite <strong>poles</strong> of the cell. This separation <strong>reduces</strong> the chromosome number by half, ensuring genetic diversity in the resulting cells.</p>


    <p style="font-weight: bold; color: #222; background-color: #ff3b86; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;">
      üöÄ Drag and drop the events happening during Anaphase I!
