  <!-- Page 11: Telophase I -->
  <div class="page" id="page11">
    <h1>‚ûî Telophase I</h1>
    <p>During <strong>Telophase</strong> I of meiosis, the <strong>separated homologous</strong> chromosomes <strong>reach</strong> the opposite <strong>poles</strong> of the cell. The <strong>nuclear envelope</strong> begins to <strong>reform</strong> around each set of chromosomes, The chromosomes begins to <strong>decondense</strong>, and the cell prepares to divide.</p>


    <p style="font-weight: bold; color: #222; background-color: #ff3b86; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;">
