  <!-- Page 12: Cytokinesis -->
  <div class="page" id="page12">
    <h1>‚ûî Cytokinesis</h1>
    <p><strong>Cytokinesis</strong> I is the final step of Meiosis I. The <strong>cytoplasm</strong> of the cell <strong>divides</strong>, creating two daughter cells. This process involves the formation of a <strong>cleavage furrow</strong>, a pinch that gradually forms along the middle of the cell Each of these cells is <strong>haploid</strong>, containing half the original number of chromosomes. Even though the cells are haploid, each chromosome still consists of two sister chromatids. These haploid cells are now ready to enter Meiosis II, where further division occurs.</p>


    <p style="font-weight: bold; color: #222; background-color: #ff3b86; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;">
      üöÄ Drag and drop the events happening during Cytokinesis!
    </p>

    <div class="drag-container">
      <div class="drag-item" id="drag1" draggable="true">
        <img src="https://github.com/70100t/meiosis/blob/main/pic9.png" alt="." width="100">
      </div>
      <div class="drag-item" id="drag2" draggable="true">
        <img src="c:/tala/pic8.png" alt="Four chromatids forming" width="100">
      </div>
    </div>


    <div class="drop-zone" id="drop-zone6">
      Drop events here!
    </div>

    <script>
