<div class="page" id="page13">
    <h1>‚ûî Prophase II</h1>
    <p>In <strong>Prophase II</strong> of meiosis, the <strong>nuclear envelope breaks</strong> down again in both <strong>haploid cells</strong>. Since <strong>DNA replication</strong> already occurred during <strong>Interphase</strong>, it doesn't happen here. The chromosomes, which are still made up of two sister chromatids, become visible once more. <strong>Spindle fibers</strong> begin to form in each cell, and these fibers attach to the <strong>centrioles</strong></p>
    
    <p style="font-weight: bold; color: #222; background-color: #ff3b86; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;"> üöÄ Drag and drop the events happening during Prophase II!</strong></p>
    
