  <!-- Nondisjunction Page -->
<div class="page" id="page16" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; text-align: center; padding: 50px; background-color: #f0f8ff;">
  <h1 style="font-size: 3em; margin-bottom: 10px;">Nondisjunction</h1>
  <h2 style="font-size: 2em; color: #ff4c4c; margin-bottom: 30px;">Oops! Something wrong happened</h2>

  <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin: 20px auto; max-width: 800px;">
    <strong>Nondisjunction</strong> happens when <strong>spindle fibers fail</strong>  to pull chromosomes apart properly during the <strong>Anaphase</strong>.
  </p>
  <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin: 20px auto; max-width: 800px;">
    As a result, chromosomes don't separate evenly into the daughter cells, causing gametes to have <strong>too many</strong> or <strong>too few</strong> chromosomes.
  </p>
  <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin: 20px auto; max-width: 800px;">
    This mistake can lead to <strong>genetic disorders</strong> like <strong>Down Syndrome</strong>, which is caused by having an <strong>extra</strong> chromosome.
  </p>

  <div class="prompt" style="margin-top: 40px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.5em;">
    Let‚Äôs keep going!
  </div>

  <div class="button-container" style="margin-top: 20px;">
