      Next: Telophase II
    </button>
  </div>
</div>


  <!-- Page 16: Telophase II -->
<div class="page" id="page17">
    <h1>‚ûî Telophase II</h1>
    <p> In <strong>Telophase II</strong> of meiosis, the chromosomes <strong>arrive</strong> at opposite poles of the cells, and the <strong>nuclear envelope reforms</strong> around <strong>each set</strong> of chromosomes. The chromosomes begin to <strong>uncoil</strong>, returning to their less condensed form. <strong>Cytokinesis</strong> divides both cells' <strong>cytoplasm</strong>, resulting in <strong>four haploid</strong> daughter cells, each with one set of chromosomes.</p>
    <p style="font-weight: bold; color: #222; background-color: #ff3b86; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;">
      üöÄ Drag and drop the events happening during Telophase II!
    </p>
